      "rationale": "Primary QoI is NIH (normalized index of hemolysis), directly linked to the regulatory acceptance criterion RH < 1. Secondary QoI is differential pressure head, confirming hydraulic fidelity. Both QoIs are standard metrics in FDA guidance for blood-contacting device CFD.",
