      "rationale": "Detailed model input uncertainty propagation is scoped out at MRL 2. Key inputs (fluid viscosity, pump geometry dimensions, rotational speed) are taken from calibrated measurements with stated uncertainties. Sensitivity of NIH to ±5% variation in viscosity was checked informally and found to be less than 3% change in NIH, confirming low input sensitivity."
